7️⃣ EVALUATION METRICS
Q20. What does ROC‑AUC mean?
Best Answer:

ROC‑AUC measures how well the model separates buyers from non‑buyers across all thresholds.
A value closer to 1 means stronger class discrimination.


Q21. Precision vs Recall – which matters more here?
Best Answer:

Recall matters more because missing a potential buyer leads to lost revenue.
Some false positives are acceptable in marketing scenarios.


8️⃣ FEATURE IMPORTANCE & INTERPRETABILITY
Q22. What did feature importance reveal?
Best Answer:

PageValues overwhelmingly dominated feature importance, followed by Month.
Technical features like Browser or OS contributed very little, confirming that user behavior matters more than device attributes.


Q23. Why is multicollinearity important?
Best Answer:

Highly correlated features like BounceRates and ExitRates can distort coefficient interpretation in linear models, but tree‑based models handle them well.


